[h4 id=Mission2:ROUTINEPATROL 
	" Mission 2: ROUTINE PATROL  
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"This mission is little bit confusing. Forcing AI to use the bayonet might look slow, but in fact if the AI leaves my units with less than 20 HP, I get an extra animation. So, using bayonet removes this animation and also leads to instant next turn (you can notice this extra animation there). Everything else is as simple as it looks.
	$LF
]p
[pre 
	$LF
]pre
[h4 id=Mission3:TRENCHWARFARE 
	" Mission 3: TRENCH WARFARE
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"This is where the magic starts.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"On the first turn I instantly kill the Grunt who acts first in the AI's squad. He is in the middle of map, so he can't attack anyone quickly and usually walks around until he's able to hit somebody with a grenade or find a weapon box containing a cluster grenade.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Instead of the Grunt, the AI thus will use his Gunner first. This is important since they have the bazooka, so they are likely to act faster than units from any other career path, so I'm totally fine with letting them act.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"On my second turn I move to another corner of the map and throw gas to poison two Grunts. This walk wastes a little bit of time, much less than letting the AI's Grunts act instead. Poisoning both Grunts forces the AI to skip the next 2 turns.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"My third turn is a big mystery. Instead of dealing 37+ damage, I managed to get some weird OOB explosion while the unit is still alive, which doesn't happen that fast anywhere else.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"The final Grunt dies because of the gas.
	$LF
]p
[pre 
	" 
	$LF
]pre
[h4 id=Mission4:MORNINGGLORY! 
	" Mission 4: MORNING GLORY!
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"I used a different career path for one of my units compared to the old run. I use only 1 Scout instead of 2 this time. Despite the fact that using 2 Scouts here lets you skip the first 2 enemy turns, it generally gives you way more profit on later missions. However, I still managed to save time here.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"I have to fight against five units, and all of them are placed across the whole map, so I can't really get under 5 turns. My target is getting the fastest possible turns for myself and the AI.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"I fight against 2 Grunts and 3 Gunners. On the first turn, I poison the Grunt who is supposed to act first, so the AI's turn is cancelled.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"For rest of the level I need to OHKO every enemy unit. I also want to cancel the death animation, so I shot them into the minefield.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"I figured out that not hiding behind mountains lets you force the AI to use pistols instead of bazooka. It's much faster, but the AI almost never misses with rifles/pistols. However, the AI ignores objects that are not part of the stage layout, so I used a tree to take all their shots without wasting time.
	$LF
]p
[pre 
	$LF
]pre
[h4 id=Mission5:ISLANDINVASION 
	" Mission 5: ISLAND INVASION
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"This mission is annoying. There is an unavoidable long AI turn for the Scout which I have to accept. It's possible to kill him before his turn, but it wastes 2 of my turns, which is always slower.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"However, I found another way to optimize the run. Instead of grinding for the fastest possible OHKO for each unit separately, I manipulated the AI to fall close to the AI's Medic twice after my shots. It let me kill him without doing anything, so I saved a turn.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Hogshead falls!
	$LF
]p
[pre 
	$LF
]pre
