[h4 id=Mission22:ASSASSINATION 
	" Mission 22: ASSASSINATION
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"The last of the "3 most complicated missions" in the run.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"This mission is a nightmare for optimization. You need to fight against only 4 units, but:
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"1: A Scout is hiding with 20 extra HP.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"2: A Hero is sitting inside a shelter with 100 extra HP.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"3/4: Gunners are sitting inside artillery with 200 extra HP each.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Destroying each artillery requires a lot of time even with the best possible shots, so I found another way to win.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"First of all, I put my Hero inside the pillbox which the Scout is supposed to take on the AI's first turn and used an airstrike to kill the Scout and deal some damage to the enemy's shelter. I also forced the AI to leave his artillery on his first turn.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"On my second turn I move my Hero to the left corner and kill the first Gunner with a bazooka. The purpose of this movement is to hide my Hero from the artillery and manipulate the AI to deal maximum damage to my Pyrotechnic and some damage to the shelter on the next turn. I sacrifice my unit instead of moving him to safety because it's faster.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"The shelter is weak on the 3rd turn, so I can OHKO the AI's Hero inside with an airburst now.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"On the AI's next turn he can't deal any damage to my units from the artillery, so he has to jump out and grab some loot. The closest one is a jetpack. He doesn't have time for other boxes, so he has to attack at the end of his turn. It makes him a very vulnerable target, which was his final mistake.
	$LF
]p
[pre 
	$LF
]pre
